 individual bronze - in the garden of France's famous Sun King atParis 2024.\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 653, \"end\": 666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"score\": 0.9999948522782397, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Collett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Collett\"}, {\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7833612098782681, \"rank\": 0.13978180649301344, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her prince\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 685}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"another Olympic team title - and individual bronze\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 763}, {\"ngram\": \"the garden\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 779}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Louis XIV's palace seems the fitting venue forTeam GBto make the top of the podium for the first time in Paris, meaning they remain the only nation that has won a gold medal at every Olympics dating back to 1896.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"score\": 0.999999999911779, \"rank\": 8.828673453199653e-11, \"text\": \"Louis XIV\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_XIV\"}, {\"begin\": 928, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.27665065290092e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fitting venue forTeam GBto\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"the top\", \"from\": 884, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 895, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"the first time\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"the only nation\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 970}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 996}, {\"ngram\": \"every Olympics\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1014}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Collett and Tom McEwen won team gold three years ago in Tokyo and joined forces with Ros Canter to defend their title, as hosts France and Japan completed the podium.\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1049, \"end\": 1059, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"score\": 0.8873196584612367, \"rank\": 0.07814407814405706, \"text\": \"Tom McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q378622\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_McEwen_(drag_racer)\"}, {\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999080388761163, \"rank\": 9.196585697180506e-05, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1165, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7833612098782681, \"rank\": 0.13978180649301344, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1176, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9453098228038023, \"rank\": 0.037900953708945175, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1044}, {\"ngram\": \"team gold\", \"from\": 1064, \"to\": 1073}, {\"ngram\": \"forces\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1116}, {\"ngram\": \"Ros Canter\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1132}, {\"ngram\": \"their title\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1154}, {\"ngram\": \"hosts\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1164}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1192, \"to\": 1202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And then Collett came back to ride her second flawless round on London 52 - who she nicknames Dan - to claim individual bronze.\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999900001058, \"rank\": 4.9565273214335144e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1221}, {\"ngram\": \"her second flawless round\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"individual bronze\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1331}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I wanted to have been sat on a nervous horse but thankfully he rose to the occasion,\\\" said Collett.\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a nervous horse\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1379}, {\"ngram\": \"the occasion\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1418}, {\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He loves showing off and he thinks he's right at home with the palace in the background and everyone watching him.\", \"from\": 1436, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 1486, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"the palace\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1506}, {\"ngram\": \"the background\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's waited three years for a full stadium.\", \"from\": 1552, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a full stadium\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The noise was unreal, but it did not distract him at all.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The noise\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1607}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He's a true professional and I think he knew what was at stake.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1719, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"stake\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I would not wanted to have sat on any other horse.\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any other horse\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 1769}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We knew coming here we stood a good chance because the horsepower Team GB has at the moment is second to none, we could have fielded another team with the reserves as they could have won a gold medal.\", \"from\": 1772, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999987712570149, \"rank\": 1.228752027816938e-05, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good chance\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1815}, {\"ngram\": \"the horsepower\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1838}, {\"ngram\": \"the moment\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"none\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1882}, {\"ngram\": \"another team\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 1918}, {\"ngram\": \"the reserves\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1936}, {\"ngram\": \"a gold medal\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's quite a strange feeling winning two medals, I had about five minutes to enjoy that team gold, two Olympic medals is something I'd never even dream about.\\\"\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"quite a strange feeling\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2004}, {\"ngram\": \"two medals\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2023}, {\"ngram\": \"about five minutes\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2049}, {\"ngram\": \"that team gold\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"two Olympic medals\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2093}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been a difficult few days for the British equestrian team in Paris, following the suspension of six-time Olympic dressage medallist Charlotte Dujardin, after footage emerged of her repeatedly whipping a horse in training.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 9.27665065290092e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2292, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Charlotte Dujardin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charlotte_Dujardin\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a difficult few days\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2167}, {\"ngram\": \"the British equestrian team\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"the suspension\", \"from\": 2220, \"to\": 2234}, {\"ngram\": \"footage\", \"from\": 2300, \"to\": 2307}, {\"ngram\": \"a horse\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2362}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Collett insists the team's performance would not be possible if horses were mistreated.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2456, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 2369, \"to\": 2376}, {\"ngram\": \"the team's performance\", \"from\": 2385, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"horses\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's huge for our sport for people to see our horses go out there and look a million dollars,\\\" she added, \\\"There is a huge team behind us that make it possible, and horses do not perform like that if they are not happy.\", \"from\": 2458, \"to\": 2679, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our sport\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2482}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2487, \"to\": 2493}, {\"ngram\": \"our horses\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2511}, {\"ngram\": \"a million dollars\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2551}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge team\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2586}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2594, \"to\": 2596}, {\"ngram\": \"horses\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Our job was to focus on our horses and show the world that they are the real stars of the show, we are just the ones that get to enjoy these moments on them.\\\"\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2840, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our job\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2689}, {\"ngram\": \"our horses\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2716}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2726, \"to\": 2735}, {\"ngram\": \"the real stars\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2764}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2776}, {\"ngram\": \"just the ones\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2798}, {\"ngram\": \"these moments\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain had a slender five-point advantage heading into the decisive jumping after Canter picked up just four penalties and McEwen went clear, meaning Collett had the luxury of knowing she could knock down four fences and still win.\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 3074, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2842, \"end\": 2849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9243136312589222, \"rank\": 0.08185892512907553, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2966, \"end\": 2972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.995493243301195e-15, \"text\": \"McEwen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robbie_McEwen\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a slender five-point advantage\", \"from\": 2854, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"the decisive jumping\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 2918}, {\"ngram\": \"Canter\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2931}, {\"ngram\": \"just four penalties\", \"from\": 2942, \"to\": 2961}, {\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 2993, \"to\": 3000}, {\"ngram\": \"the luxury\", \"from\": 3005, \"to\": 3015}, {\"ngram\": \"four fences\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's final rider whipped up the crowd as Collett entered the area, the Entente Cordiale creaking, but Collett and London 52 were nerveless under the most intense pressure.\", \"from\": 3076, \"to\": 3251, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3076, \"end\": 3082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.7833612098782681, \"rank\": 0.13978180649301344, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3194, \"end\": 3200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999900001058, \"rank\": 4.9565273214335144e-09, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the crowd\", \"from\": 3108, \"to\": 3117}, {\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 3121, \"to\": 3128}, {\"ngram\": \"the area\", \"from\": 3137, \"to\": 3145}, {\"ngram\": \"Collett\", \"from\": 3182, \"to\": 3189}, {\"ngram\": \"the most int